WEBVTT

02:15.343 --> 02:17.376
Give it up, Frank!

02:37.365 --> 02:38.562
- Joe Cribbens.

02:40.225 --> 02:43.600
- Joe Cribbens! Visitor!

02:47.606 --> 02:50.970
- Well, goddamn. Hard to figure
who I'd less rather see.

02:52.710 --> 02:54.611
What brings a skunk
like you here?

02:54.646 --> 02:57.878
- I was in the neighborhood
collecting reward money.

02:57.913 --> 02:59.583
Thought I'd pay you a visit.

02:59.618 --> 03:03.356
- Yeah. Heard you took down
Frank Ledbetter last week.

03:03.391 --> 03:07.327
We get all the news in here.
You'd be surprised.

03:08.759 --> 03:11.089
How much you gonna collect
for old Frank?

03:11.124 --> 03:14.301
Friend of yours?
- Never met the man,

03:14.336 --> 03:16.094
but I was on his side.

03:18.406 --> 03:22.100
Okay, bounty man. Did you give
him much of a chance?

03:22.135 --> 03:23.970
- Same chance he gave me.

03:26.942 --> 03:28.909
- Give it up, Frank!

03:31.914 --> 03:35.916
- Right. Just another fella
dead for a dollar.

03:35.951 --> 03:40.019
I figure you know I'm getting
out of here next week.

03:40.791 --> 03:44.496
Served my time. All five years.

03:44.531 --> 03:46.300
- I heard you've been
telling people

03:46.335 --> 03:48.302
first thing you were gonna do
when you walk out of here

03:48.337 --> 03:50.766
is get a gun and look me up.

03:50.801 --> 03:52.570
- Don't flatter yourself.

03:52.605 --> 03:54.803
I'm not going out of my way
to find you.

03:55.872 --> 03:58.444
I'm going to head down
to Mexico.

03:58.479 --> 04:01.810
Just... play out the string.

04:01.845 --> 04:04.945
Cards, tequila, seÃ±oritas...

04:04.980 --> 04:07.079
- No matter where you're headed,

04:07.114 --> 04:10.885
you'll still end up the same.
Horse thief.

04:12.317 --> 04:14.625
- Guilty.
- Bank robber.

04:15.221 --> 04:17.958
- Couldn't prove it.
- Killed a couple of men.

04:18.499 --> 04:20.961
- Couldn't prove it,
and I never killed nobody

04:20.996 --> 04:23.337
that wasn't trying to kill me.

04:31.842 --> 04:34.876
When you took me down,
I was sleeping.

04:36.242 --> 04:37.780
It wasn't a real fight.

04:37.815 --> 04:41.388
I just... woke up with a gun
in my face.

04:41.423 --> 04:43.214
- Stay clear of me, Joe.

04:44.349 --> 04:45.854
- You do the same!

04:46.890 --> 04:50.595
Otherwise, most likely,
you're a dead man.

04:52.225 --> 04:56.436
- I don't usually tell a man
twice. Stay clear of me, Joe.

05:03.104 --> 05:04.576
- Shit heel.

05:28.195 --> 05:31.801
- Prisoner number 387,
Joe Cribbens.

05:34.234 --> 05:36.905
Your paperwork came
in the afternoon mail.

05:36.940 --> 05:38.907
Tomorrow morning 10 o'clock,

05:38.942 --> 05:41.008
you get your possessions back
and a government check

05:41.043 --> 05:44.110
for 50 dollars.
Good luck to you, Joe.

05:44.145 --> 05:45.452
- Yes, sir.

05:46.884 --> 05:48.081
Yip!

06:12.107 --> 06:13.777
Take a last look.

06:36.769 --> 06:39.638
Captain Brand.
Rider approaching, sir.

06:48.308 --> 06:51.012
Good morning.
Let me take care of your horse.

06:57.383 --> 06:59.790
Max Borlund, follow us.

07:08.361 --> 07:11.131
Sir. Mr. Borlund, sir.

07:11.166 --> 07:12.803
- As you were, corporal.

07:15.808 --> 07:19.678
Mr. Borlund. It's good
to see you again.

07:19.713 --> 07:22.043
It's been some time.
- It has.

07:22.078 --> 07:25.519
- This is Martin Kidd. He could
stand to use your services.

07:25.554 --> 07:27.884
Mr. Kidd is a prominent
businessman here

07:27.919 --> 07:30.381
in the territory,
and a friend to the army.

07:31.890 --> 07:35.155
- Mr. Borlund, it seems your
reputation precedes you.

07:35.190 --> 07:36.893
- I'll accept that
as a compliment.

07:36.928 --> 07:39.060
- Gentlemen, this is
a clandestine moment

07:39.095 --> 07:41.568
and a meeting
that never happened.

07:41.603 --> 07:44.461
That's why I've convened it out
here in the middle of nowhere.

07:44.496 --> 07:46.903
I'll let you two
get down to business.

07:46.938 --> 07:50.874
- Um, Mr. Borlund, I doubt
that you're familiar

07:50.909 --> 07:53.173
with a Buffalo soldier
by the name of Elijah Jones?

07:53.208 --> 07:54.977
Private Elijah Jones? No?

07:55.012 --> 07:58.376
<i>Right, he's taken a white woman,</i>
<i>my wife, Rachel.</i>

07:58.411 --> 08:00.818
<i>Abducted her three weeks ago,</i>

08:00.853 --> 08:03.249
<i>took her across the border</i>
<i>down to Mexico.</i>

08:03.284 --> 08:06.483
<i>- I sent out patrols,</i>
<i>thought we could head 'em off,</i>

08:06.518 --> 08:09.596
find 'em before they got
to the border. We missed 'em.

08:09.631 --> 08:12.159
- Alright, so, son of a bitch
is asking for $10,000

08:12.194 --> 08:13.996
in ransom money,
which I will not pay.

08:14.031 --> 08:17.604
I do not reward criminals,
but I am willing to offer you

08:17.639 --> 08:22.070
$2,000 to bring Rachel back.
$500 advance.

08:27.440 --> 08:30.617
This will help you
identify Rachel.

08:30.652 --> 08:33.587
Captain Brand there
has a document stating

08:33.622 --> 08:36.249
that you are a representative
of the United States government

08:36.284 --> 08:38.625
and you're in pursuit of Elijah,
in case you run into any

08:38.660 --> 08:41.254
legal problems down in Mexico.

08:41.289 --> 08:43.564
- Well, three weeks head
start...

08:44.490 --> 08:48.063
I need supplies, a pack mule,
ammunition.

08:48.098 --> 08:51.561
- Discretion in this matter,
that's of paramount importance.

08:51.596 --> 08:54.498
It's my wife's reputation
to consider.

08:55.567 --> 08:57.468
As well as my own.

08:57.503 --> 08:58.678
- Sergeant Poe!

08:59.947 --> 09:02.473
- Off the books, we're sending
one soldier to accompany you.

09:04.609 --> 09:08.314
- Sir! Mr. Borlund,
as ordered by the captain,

09:08.349 --> 09:10.756
Sergeant Alonzo Poe
reporting for duty, sir!

09:12.452 --> 09:14.628
Make sure
he dresses civilian.

09:14.663 --> 09:16.663
Things need to look proper.

09:16.698 --> 09:18.390
Don't want you two
to travel together

09:18.425 --> 09:19.930
until you're both south
of the border.

09:19.965 --> 09:22.526
- Yes, Sergeant.
- Sir, yes, sir!

09:38.379 --> 09:41.853
Well, well. Here comes
the bounty man.

09:43.318 --> 09:45.087
Captain say he the best shooter
in the territory,

09:45.122 --> 09:46.627
rifle or pistol.

09:59.301 --> 10:00.498
- Sergeant Poe.

10:01.567 --> 10:02.566
- Mr. Borlund, sir.

10:03.877 --> 10:06.141
- The captain tells me
you're gonna be a very

10:06.176 --> 10:07.945
valuable man on this trip.

10:07.980 --> 10:10.013
- I just want to say
if things get tight,

10:10.048 --> 10:12.642
I'm a damn good shot.
Best eye in the regiment.

10:12.677 --> 10:15.117
- Captain also says

10:15.152 --> 10:18.791
you have an idea where Mrs. Kidd
and this Elijah Jones may be.

10:18.826 --> 10:21.893
- Oh, I know exactly where.
Got the map right here.

10:23.094 --> 10:24.324
Can't do much better than that,

10:24.359 --> 10:25.556
now can you?

10:25.591 --> 10:27.195
Shows you right to where
they're hiding out.

10:27.230 --> 10:28.526
Now, this here map
was given to me

10:28.561 --> 10:29.967
by Private Elijah Jones himself.

10:30.002 --> 10:31.661
- Private Jones
just hands out maps

10:31.696 --> 10:33.872
of where he's gonna be
after he deserts the army

10:33.907 --> 10:36.534
and abducts a white woman?
Let me see this map.

10:46.513 --> 10:49.921
According to this,
they're deep into Chihuahua.

10:49.956 --> 10:52.055
- Mm-hmm.
That sounds about right.

10:52.090 --> 10:54.024
Elijah said it was a fair piece.

10:54.895 --> 10:58.358
- Look, normally we'd head
straight to San Juanito.

10:58.393 --> 11:00.096
It's the best road south.

11:00.901 --> 11:03.836
Start asking if anyone's seen
a Black man travelling

11:03.871 --> 11:06.201
with a white woman,
but if he abducted her,

11:06.236 --> 11:08.335
he'd avoid showing up in cities.

11:08.370 --> 11:12.537
- No. He run off,
damn foolish. But...

11:13.947 --> 11:16.046
Well, Elijah didn't
abduct nobody.

11:17.478 --> 11:19.049
- That's not what
I've been told.

11:20.415 --> 11:21.953
- Let me tell you about Elijah.

11:22.615 --> 11:26.188
Like all of God's children,
he's got his faults.

11:26.223 --> 11:28.223
But in a lot of ways,
he's a really good fella.

11:30.293 --> 11:33.800
I know these is delicate
matters, but I gotta say,

11:33.835 --> 11:36.462
if she's with Elijah,
it's 'cause she wanna be.

11:37.069 --> 11:38.838
- Sounds like
you're defending him.

11:40.666 --> 11:42.369
- Private Elijah Jones
was expecting me

11:42.404 --> 11:45.174
to join up with him. Gave me
the map so I could find the way.

11:45.847 --> 11:49.079
Now I'm the one who's supposed
to deliver the ransom money.

11:49.114 --> 11:52.214
That's why I truly do believe
they are holed up

11:52.249 --> 11:55.085
in the middle of nowhere
at an American fella's place,

11:55.120 --> 11:56.614
named Hannon.

11:56.649 --> 12:00.123
- There's a Hannon
that's a wanted man in Texas.

12:00.158 --> 12:02.257
The poster's been up
for five years.

12:02.292 --> 12:05.590
Accomplice to murder.
Bank robbery in El Paso.

12:06.868 --> 12:08.329
Do you know this woman?
Mm-hmm.

12:08.364 --> 12:09.759
Ain't never met her.

12:09.794 --> 12:12.300
She helped improve Elijah's
reading in the school.

12:12.335 --> 12:13.873
At least that's what he told me.

12:14.843 --> 12:18.207
- Yeah, is this the face that
launched a thousand ships?

12:19.441 --> 12:21.342
- You wanna run that by me
one more time?

12:21.883 --> 12:24.345
- Ah, it's a line by Marlowe,
Shakespeare's time,

12:24.380 --> 12:26.248
you know, about Helen of Troy.

12:26.283 --> 12:28.283
- All right, right, right, I was
just reading all about that

12:28.318 --> 12:29.350
just the other day.

12:30.122 --> 12:32.485
- You trust that map?
- Mm-hmm.

12:33.620 --> 12:34.927
And they're holed up down there

12:34.962 --> 12:36.489
waiting for the money
that I ain't bringing.

12:38.625 --> 12:43.001
Ooh! Yes, sir! I guess you wanna
know my story too, huh?

12:43.036 --> 12:45.300
- Not necessarily.
- Oh, come on, now, Mr. Borlund.

12:45.335 --> 12:47.104
A little friendly talk
to help the time pass by.

12:47.139 --> 12:48.303
Ain't that true?

12:48.338 --> 12:50.041
- Thanks.
- You want me to call you Max?

12:54.509 --> 12:56.674
- I think Mr. Borlund
will do just fine.

12:57.512 --> 12:59.215
- Mr. Borlund it is.

12:59.250 --> 13:01.481
See now, the thing with Elijah
here is real simple.

13:02.055 --> 13:03.351
He wasn't an army man.

13:04.057 --> 13:06.519
See, where I come from,
a new bed,

13:06.554 --> 13:09.863
clean clothes, a good horse,
and three square meals a day

13:09.898 --> 13:11.524
sounded like
a mighty fine deal.

13:11.559 --> 13:13.724
I joined up in the army
when I was 17.

13:14.694 --> 13:17.629
The captain, he filled me in
about you too now, sir.

13:17.664 --> 13:21.303
Captain say you either a
Dutchman, or a Swede, or a...

13:21.338 --> 13:22.832
a German or something such.

13:22.867 --> 13:25.175
Captain say you used to be
a soldier some time way back.

13:25.210 --> 13:26.803
Ain't too sure about
which army, though.

13:26.838 --> 13:28.838
- Mm-hmm.
- Mind telling me?

13:28.873 --> 13:32.380
Is you a Dutchman or a Swede?
Whatever?

13:32.415 --> 13:34.888
- Not at all. I'm an American.

13:54.371 --> 13:55.700
- You know, uh...

13:57.209 --> 13:59.374
You've been acting real jumpy
the last few days.

14:02.742 --> 14:04.709
- I've come to realize...

14:06.647 --> 14:09.285
...my whole life, I've done
impulsive things.

14:11.718 --> 14:14.059
They don't always work out.

14:16.063 --> 14:18.228
Got a reserve of 20 bullets.

14:19.099 --> 14:21.165
I'm gonna use another five
to practice.

14:22.069 --> 14:24.729
I keep being told this is
a dangerous country.

14:36.941 --> 14:40.019
I'll never give them the
pleasure of watching me cry.

14:40.318 --> 14:43.781
- Good. Yeah, I like that.

14:44.685 --> 14:46.421
We did what we done.

14:46.456 --> 14:48.995
And we just saying
to all of them,

14:49.030 --> 14:50.590
"Piss upon ya.

14:51.692 --> 14:53.263
Go straight to hell."

15:08.181 --> 15:11.809
- I was sent here by Tiberio
because my English is good.

15:11.844 --> 15:13.646
Very good, as you can tell.

15:14.319 --> 15:18.519
Let me begin saying I am honored
to meet you, Mrs. Kidd.

15:18.554 --> 15:21.621
Obviously, a very kind and
beautiful woman.

15:22.624 --> 15:25.361
- I say thank you, Mr. Romero.

15:25.396 --> 15:27.330
But maybe you should get
to the point.

15:28.036 --> 15:29.365
Why are you here?

15:29.862 --> 15:32.533
- Oh. I'm here to represent
Tiberio Vargas,

15:32.568 --> 15:35.602
and to give response
to the financial offer

15:35.637 --> 15:37.604
made to him by SeÃ±or Hannon.

15:37.639 --> 15:39.177
Let us review the facts.

15:39.212 --> 15:41.476
- We don't have to do
this business here and now,

15:41.511 --> 15:42.873
in front of these people.

15:43.843 --> 15:45.876
- Mr. Hannon owes Tiberio Vargas

15:45.911 --> 15:47.779
several thousand dollars
in gambling debt.

15:47.814 --> 15:52.223
- Hold on, goddamn it!
This is between me and Tiberio.

15:52.258 --> 15:56.359
- To retire the debt, Mr. Hannon
has offered Tiberio Vargas

15:56.394 --> 15:59.956
$5,000 of Mrs. Kidd's
ransom money,

15:59.991 --> 16:03.201
in return for your safe passage
to Veracruz and then Cuba.

16:03.731 --> 16:07.568
- Goddamn it. You son
of a bitch, you sold us out.

16:08.901 --> 16:10.043
- All right...

16:10.936 --> 16:12.540
I needed money.

16:12.575 --> 16:16.808
The two of you, you eat up
my food, sleep all hours.

16:16.843 --> 16:18.579
You don't pay shit for rent.

16:19.285 --> 16:23.980
And worst of all, I gotta deal
with this hell cat of yours

16:24.015 --> 16:26.917
complaining all the time
about how dirty it is

16:26.952 --> 16:31.361
for her dainty self and that I
live like a goddamn bindlestiff!

16:31.396 --> 16:33.858
I don't see why I gotta
put up with this shit

16:33.893 --> 16:35.926
from this rich bitch whore

16:35.961 --> 16:37.763
without getting paid
royal for it!

16:45.608 --> 16:49.038
I've decided...
the price for room and board

16:49.073 --> 16:52.580
for these two runaways
is $2,500.

16:53.385 --> 16:56.584
Everybody in this deal
is guaranteed something.

16:57.081 --> 16:58.586
Everybody benefits.

16:59.457 --> 17:01.754
- I'll tell you
about guarantees.

17:01.789 --> 17:03.294
I'll guarantee you this.

17:03.989 --> 17:06.759
I am not a whore.

17:28.079 --> 17:32.290
- A message is sent
to Tiberio by SeÃ±or Hannon.

17:32.754 --> 17:36.052
His offer proposes that Tiberio,
for $5,000,

17:36.087 --> 17:40.694
will guarantee safe conduct for
you and Mrs. Kidd to Veracruz.

17:41.796 --> 17:43.796
I have come here to
tell you that

17:43.831 --> 17:46.634
Tiberio accepts your proposal.

17:50.277 --> 17:51.936
- Maybe this actually works.

17:52.642 --> 17:56.314
Sure, we lose some money, but...
it gets us a clean getaway.

18:26.214 --> 18:27.510
- Mr. Borlund.

18:36.323 --> 18:39.192
Outlaws?
- Until proven differently.

18:59.676 --> 19:00.708
- Greetings.

19:02.074 --> 19:03.876
This is SeÃ±or Tiberio Vargas,

19:03.911 --> 19:06.516
I am Esteban Romero,
at your service.

19:06.551 --> 19:08.320
I will translate.

19:08.355 --> 19:12.225
SeÃ±or Vargas is a very important
and generous man.

19:12.260 --> 19:15.426
Ten years ago, he sent me
to Monterrey to study law.

19:28.034 --> 19:31.002
As you can see,
Tiberio is hunting,

19:31.037 --> 19:32.938
entertaining his guest and
business associate,

19:32.973 --> 19:34.577
SeÃ±or Palmer.

19:34.612 --> 19:37.712
SeÃ±or Palmer has come
all the way from London

19:37.747 --> 19:39.714
to do business with Tiberio.

19:39.749 --> 19:42.079
- Really?
- Uh, Tiberio says

19:42.114 --> 19:43.916
that the land
you're travelling through,

19:43.951 --> 19:46.919
the water you're helping
yourselves to is all his,

19:46.954 --> 19:51.594
and as a result, there is a fee
to be paid for safe passage.

19:55.061 --> 19:56.863
Tiberio is not happy.

19:56.898 --> 19:59.965
He says force
could possibly be used.

20:00.000 --> 20:01.439
He has many guns.

20:01.903 --> 20:04.970
- So do we. Tiberio will be
the first one to be shot.

20:05.005 --> 20:07.973
- If you allow me, sir,
I don't mean to interfere,

20:08.008 --> 20:11.075
but it might not be wise
to contest this issue.

20:11.110 --> 20:14.320
Now, if you want my opinion--
- I don't.

20:16.654 --> 20:19.490
Mr. Poe!
- That'll be me, sir.

20:19.525 --> 20:21.426
Armed and ready.

20:24.794 --> 20:27.729
Down here,
the gringos are not the boss.

20:27.764 --> 20:30.699
- So you do speak English.
- Only when I want.

20:42.383 --> 20:43.679
- Who the hell are you?

20:44.682 --> 20:47.111
- I'm the fella with the gun.
Who the hell is you?

20:47.146 --> 20:49.080
- I go by Jack Tyree.

20:49.115 --> 20:51.214
- Looks like you a long way
from home, Jack.

20:52.217 --> 20:54.217
- I'm giving you advice, amigo.

20:55.187 --> 20:59.332
Clear on out of here. Tiberio
don't kill you, I just might.

20:59.367 --> 21:02.368
I don't much like me some damned
smart mouthed fucker.

21:09.135 --> 21:10.343
- So, what's it gonna be?

21:11.203 --> 21:12.477
How do you want to play it?

21:29.155 --> 21:31.826
Tiberio asks if
you, like so many others,

21:31.861 --> 21:33.663
are here to seek gold.

21:33.698 --> 21:35.533
- We all work for money.

21:43.543 --> 21:46.907
Well, sir,
my name is William Palmer.

21:47.338 --> 21:49.415
I just wish to say that
your good fortune matches

21:49.450 --> 21:51.043
your obstinate stupidity.

21:51.584 --> 21:53.551
<i>- Vamos, vamos!</i>
- Good day.

21:54.422 --> 21:55.586
Yah!

21:58.426 --> 22:01.394
- You find gold,
you must share it with Tiberio.

22:02.023 --> 22:04.760
Otherwise, I guarantee
the consequences will be

22:04.795 --> 22:06.630
extremely unpleasant.

22:22.241 --> 22:24.417
- I don't think we made
a new friend.

23:01.588 --> 23:03.654
Do you wish
for a meal or a room?

23:03.689 --> 23:05.117
- I reckon I need both.

23:05.152 --> 23:07.383
- Ah. How long are you
gonna stay, SeÃ±or?

23:07.418 --> 23:10.595
- Ah, a couple of weeks.
