stay out of trouble.

24:08.149 --> 24:11.821
- See them two horses down
there? Them is army horses.

24:12.516 --> 24:13.757
The map worked out.

24:14.661 --> 24:16.287
We got 'em, Mr. Borlund.

24:16.322 --> 24:18.223
We got 'em with the element
of surprise.

24:19.864 --> 24:24.229
- The map was correct.
Very good, Mr. Poe. Very good.

24:25.100 --> 24:26.572
- I aim to please.

24:58.639 --> 25:01.772
- Don't seem
to be any luck. Shit.

25:03.270 --> 25:05.369
- You got a bad temper, Jack.

25:06.273 --> 25:09.208
The other night,
you were way out of hand.

25:11.751 --> 25:13.443
You oughta get it under control.

25:14.446 --> 25:16.281
I still can't accept--

25:22.091 --> 25:25.290
- Elijah, don't!
I wouldn't try anything foolish.

25:25.325 --> 25:26.797
Walk away from that gun.

25:26.832 --> 25:29.228
No, no, no, no!
This ain't part of the deal!

25:29.263 --> 25:30.636
This is my private fucking--

25:30.671 --> 25:33.397
- Oh, Mr. Hannon, keep
your arms up and stay quiet!

25:33.432 --> 25:34.904
- Who are you?
- Go easy now, ma'am,

25:34.939 --> 25:37.203
a lot of guns in here.
- Damn you, I asked who are you.

25:37.238 --> 25:38.567
Just what do you think
you're doing?

25:38.602 --> 25:40.206
- We're here on full legal
authority, Mrs. Kidd.

25:40.241 --> 25:42.109
- That, and me and Elijah here
are old friends.

25:42.144 --> 25:44.947
- Alonzo, you done gone over,
you done sold me out?

25:44.982 --> 25:47.818
- Yep! Turns out I'm just a good
old army man, ain't that right?

25:47.853 --> 25:49.886
- You're the only damn person
in the regiment I trusted!

25:49.921 --> 25:52.086
You let me down, brother!
- You let yourself down

25:52.121 --> 25:54.220
with this dumbass plan.
That and getting caught up

25:54.255 --> 25:55.793
with this silly-ass white woman.

25:56.290 --> 25:58.631
- One thing is for certain,
I ain't going back to Texas

25:58.666 --> 26:00.490
with some bounty man!

26:01.768 --> 26:03.163
I got a rope waiting for me.

26:03.198 --> 26:05.495
Get the hell gone
or I'll kill her, sure as hell!

26:05.530 --> 26:07.299
- He's not after you,
he's after us.

26:07.334 --> 26:08.564
- Bullshit!
- Goddamn--

26:23.647 --> 26:24.723
- You killed him.

26:25.154 --> 26:26.285
- Yes, I did.

26:27.321 --> 26:29.453
You're gonna bury him,
Mr. Jones.

26:31.699 --> 26:33.897
Max Borlund. Ma'am.

26:35.329 --> 26:38.033
I've been hired by your husband
to take you home.

27:04.259 --> 27:06.193
- You see the mess
you done got yourself in?

27:06.734 --> 27:09.031
You ain't nothing
but a damn stupid fool.

27:18.944 --> 27:21.208
- I'm not grateful
for your mission here.

27:22.112 --> 27:25.179
But I should thank you
for possibly saving my life.

27:26.116 --> 27:27.984
- Hannon was a foolish man.

27:28.019 --> 27:30.349
- Mr. Hannon was
a treacherous man.

27:32.122 --> 27:33.891
- Get yourself together,
Mrs. Kidd,

27:33.926 --> 27:36.454
and whatever you need,
we ride within the hour.

27:38.458 --> 27:41.096
- I suppose I need
to surrender my gun.

27:41.131 --> 27:43.593
I keep a derringer in my valise.

27:49.810 --> 27:51.876
I'm doing this because
Elijah might

27:51.911 --> 27:53.944
try to do something foolish.

27:54.705 --> 27:56.276
I wouldn't want
to see him killed.

27:57.642 --> 27:59.675
I'd feel more than
partially responsible

27:59.710 --> 28:01.248
if he came to any harm.

28:01.789 --> 28:05.417
- Deserted the army,
attempted extortion.

28:05.452 --> 28:07.221
He's coming in
for a lot of harm.

28:07.718 --> 28:10.719
- Maybe the easiest way out
of this mess is to shoot you.

28:10.754 --> 28:13.095
And solve at least
some of my problems.

28:13.801 --> 28:16.296
- I don't think that's such
a good idea, Mrs. Kidd.

28:27.276 --> 28:30.508
- Mr. Borlund,
I have a question.

28:32.776 --> 28:36.085
Are you under the impression
that you are rescuing me?

28:36.582 --> 28:38.153
- I was told
that you were abducted.

28:38.782 --> 28:40.254
- That was a lie.

28:40.289 --> 28:43.257
- I've also been told that
by Sergeant Poe.

29:30.801 --> 29:33.373
- When you killed Mr. Hannon
back at his cabin...

29:33.408 --> 29:34.308
- Mm-hmm.

29:35.509 --> 29:38.279
- Your bullets missed
my head by inches.

29:38.314 --> 29:39.379
- Mm-hmm.

29:41.350 --> 29:43.482
- You're that confident
in your marksmanship?

29:44.188 --> 29:45.154
- No.

29:49.930 --> 29:51.259
- Thought you was my friend.

29:52.856 --> 29:54.757
You went and turned
your back on me.

30:00.039 --> 30:01.566
- Now, you listen
to me, brother.

30:02.404 --> 30:03.766
This thing ain't over yet.

30:04.868 --> 30:06.802
I might just be able
to get you out of this mess

30:06.837 --> 30:08.177
you done put yourself in.

30:09.444 --> 30:10.916
Oh, and let me say this.

30:11.743 --> 30:14.249
I still think it's a good idea
you and the army is finished.

30:15.120 --> 30:17.384
You wasn't exactly
the soldier type of fella.

30:18.552 --> 30:20.684
I go along with the notion
seeing it's a real good idea

30:20.719 --> 30:23.456
that you end up in Cuba
some such. You hear me?

30:25.361 --> 30:26.932
- Maybe you oughta hear this.

30:27.693 --> 30:29.935
I got me and Rachel
an insurance policy.

30:30.729 --> 30:32.267
His name is Tiberio.

30:34.634 --> 30:36.106
- You know I'm married.

30:38.077 --> 30:40.737
Certainly, you know I've run off
with a man of color.

30:41.641 --> 30:44.642
I expect you think you have me
pretty well figured out.

30:48.582 --> 30:52.023
- Your husband hired me to take
you back across the border.

30:52.058 --> 30:54.322
Beyond that,
I have no opinion.

30:55.292 --> 30:57.787
- Martin Kidd is not simply
a bad husband.

30:58.790 --> 31:00.999
He's also a very bad man.

31:03.102 --> 31:05.399
- Not everyone I work for
is a saint.

31:06.666 --> 31:09.568
I took a job and I intend
to earn my money.

31:10.978 --> 31:12.769
- You live by a code?

31:13.244 --> 31:14.375
- I try.

31:14.410 --> 31:16.080
- You ever question it?

31:16.742 --> 31:18.082
- Not often.

31:19.283 --> 31:20.777
- Got a wife?

31:27.258 --> 31:29.819
- I don't think I'm a good fit
for the whole idea.

31:29.854 --> 31:30.963
- Yeah, well...

31:31.922 --> 31:33.757
- Excuse me, I gotta see
Mr. Poe.

31:44.506 --> 31:46.803
Go get something to eat,
I'll relieve you.

31:47.443 --> 31:49.575
You can spell me
in four hours, I'll wake you.

31:49.610 --> 31:52.116
- I got some information
about Elijah.

31:52.151 --> 31:53.645
The goddamn fool done made
some type of deal

31:53.680 --> 31:54.954
with that Tiberio fella.

31:56.386 --> 31:58.716
- Does... Does Mrs. Kidd
know that?

31:59.389 --> 32:02.126
- I don't know for sure,
but I expect so.

32:10.466 --> 32:12.301
- Very interesting game, poker.

32:12.864 --> 32:14.666
Sometimes, it's hard to figure

32:14.701 --> 32:18.274
when the man's bluffing
or when he's got the goods.

32:18.309 --> 32:20.309
So far,
you seem to be on your game.

32:24.348 --> 32:25.710
You know, I like to know

32:25.745 --> 32:27.613
the name of the people
I play cards with. That way,

32:27.648 --> 32:29.153
when they take my money,
it makes it that little

32:29.188 --> 32:30.517
bit more friendly.

32:30.552 --> 32:32.552
- You played here
for an hour and a half,

32:32.587 --> 32:34.719
and not knowing my name
didn't seem to bother you

32:34.754 --> 32:36.061
until I started winning.

32:36.096 --> 32:37.788
- Well, you do show some signs

32:37.823 --> 32:39.361
of being a professional
card shark.

32:39.396 --> 32:40.923
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

32:41.761 --> 32:44.696
- I'll take that
as a sign of respect.

32:44.731 --> 32:46.698
- Well, it wasn't meant
in that spirit.

32:46.733 --> 32:48.370
Now, I'd like to have a name,

32:48.405 --> 32:49.899
unless it's something
you're ashamed of.

32:49.934 --> 32:51.670
One card.

32:51.705 --> 32:52.935
- Sure thing, amigo.

32:54.873 --> 32:57.049
But I want to be real polite.

32:57.084 --> 32:58.347
You first.

32:58.844 --> 33:01.911
- With pleasure.
William Palmer Esquire,

33:01.946 --> 33:03.220
firm purchase agent for the

33:03.255 --> 33:05.013
Turnbull Mining
Properties Limited.

33:05.048 --> 33:07.257
Offices in London, Manchester,
and New Orleans.

33:07.292 --> 33:10.029
Around here, they refer to me
as Guillermo InglÃ©s.

33:10.460 --> 33:13.494
- English Bill.
Long way from home.

33:13.529 --> 33:14.627
- Indeed.

33:16.433 --> 33:17.630
And you are?

33:18.600 --> 33:21.568
- Joe Cribbens. I'm from Texas.

33:24.705 --> 33:29.114
You seem to be a man of strong
opinions, English Bill.

33:29.149 --> 33:31.545
- Mr. Palmer, if you please.

33:32.042 --> 33:34.251
Now, let me put you on notice,
Mr. Cribbens.

33:34.286 --> 33:36.044
I'm a very, very good
card player.

33:36.079 --> 33:38.552
I do not intend to be taken in
by any tricks of your trade

33:38.587 --> 33:41.093
because I am not a man
to be taken advantage of.

33:41.128 --> 33:44.096
I can defend myself adequately
here in this rough terrain.

33:44.131 --> 33:46.263
I'm also here on business
with Mr. Tiberio Vargas,

33:46.298 --> 33:47.693
who, as you must certainly know,

33:47.728 --> 33:49.662
is lord of all he surveys
in these parts.

33:50.764 --> 33:56.031
- Now, since I think you're just
another bullshit Englishman,

33:56.066 --> 33:58.638
the kind of fella
we gringos have already

33:58.673 --> 34:00.805
whipped twice in two wars...

34:02.281 --> 34:04.611
Why don't we cut the blabber

34:04.646 --> 34:07.185
and just concentrate
on playing cards?

34:11.983 --> 34:13.455
Well, hell!

34:14.084 --> 34:18.757
English Bill. Your luck's bound
to change sometime.

34:19.298 --> 34:21.628
So, I guess I'll call.

34:22.367 --> 34:25.027
With... two itty-bitty pairs.

34:28.131 --> 34:29.471
- Son of a bitch.

34:29.506 --> 34:31.605
- Some fellas just can't get
away with a bluff.

34:31.640 --> 34:33.607
They lack the character for it.

34:33.642 --> 34:34.740
- I'll tell you this
Mr. Cribbens,

34:34.775 --> 34:36.313
you're damn lucky
I'm not wearing a gun.

34:36.348 --> 34:38.150
- And I'll tell you this,
English Bill.

34:38.185 --> 34:40.416
You're damn lucky
I don't put a bullet up your ass

34:40.451 --> 34:42.110
just on general principle.

34:42.145 --> 34:47.082
Now, if I was you,
I'd get out of my sight,

34:47.117 --> 34:49.557
before I run through
all my good humor.

36:01.268 --> 36:03.862
I have
a fugitive of the law,

36:03.897 --> 36:07.206
army deserter and extortionist.

36:11.377 --> 36:15.610
I am Max Borlund representing
the United States army.

36:15.645 --> 36:18.041
- And I am Captain
Miguel Aragon.

36:18.076 --> 36:20.076
Chief Magistrate
of Trinidad Maria.

36:20.111 --> 36:21.550
- At your service.

36:21.585 --> 36:24.113
- Who's the woman?
- I have a name.

36:25.248 --> 36:27.259
Mrs. Rachel Kidd.

36:27.294 --> 36:30.427
- You can put the prisoner
in a cell and send a telegram

36:30.462 --> 36:33.188
to the territorial deputy
in Santa Fe saying that you have

36:33.223 --> 36:36.092
a Private Elijah Jones
in your custody.

36:36.127 --> 36:38.402
- You have no jurisdiction here.

36:38.437 --> 36:40.734
- Yes. But your country's law

36:40.769 --> 36:42.967
doesn't permit deserters
of foreign armies

36:43.002 --> 36:44.738
to find safe haven.

36:44.773 --> 36:48.137
There's an honorable tradition
of extraditing men

36:48.172 --> 36:49.809
who come here
with bad intentions.

36:49.844 --> 36:51.415
- Maybe you oughta
hear this, Captain.

36:51.846 --> 36:55.419
You lock me up, Tiberio Vargas
might not like it one damn bit.

36:55.454 --> 36:57.047
- Tiberio Vargas?
- Uh-huh. Me and him

36:57.082 --> 36:59.984
were talking business before
this bounty man showed up.

37:00.657 --> 37:04.153
By the way, he killed a man.
Jack Hannon.

37:08.467 --> 37:10.302
- You killed a man?
- Yeah.

37:11.261 --> 37:15.230
American. Wanted criminal
who resisted arrest.

37:15.265 --> 37:17.540
They're witnesses.
- Yes.

37:18.708 --> 37:22.039
Mr. Borlund killed Mr. Hannon
after he put a gun to my head.

37:22.712 --> 37:25.482
Mr. Borlund probably
saved my life.

37:32.117 --> 37:33.952
We are officers
of the law.

37:35.054 --> 37:36.328
We will lock him up.

37:46.637 --> 37:48.604
- Can't say I didn't do nothing
for you, brother.

37:50.575 --> 37:52.542
- Yeah, real goddamn funny.

37:52.577 --> 37:54.379
- Well, I'll check in on you
every now and then,

37:54.414 --> 37:55.875
make sure they're
feeding you proper.

38:02.213 --> 38:05.181
- Mr. Borlund,
a word in private.

38:18.537 --> 38:20.768
- I'm sorry, Elijah.

38:22.002 --> 38:23.903
None of this
is turning out right.

38:24.444 --> 38:27.544
- Yeah. Gotta admit,

38:27.579 --> 38:30.107
Cuba's looking real far away.

38:33.948 --> 38:36.916
- My government expects me
to protect lives and property.

38:36.951 --> 38:39.215
If Tiberio Vargas becomes angry,

38:39.250 --> 38:41.349
or attempts to profit
from this situation,

38:41.384 --> 38:42.889
there could be trouble.

38:42.924 --> 38:45.595
This town is under
my jurisdiction,

38:45.630 --> 38:48.290
but out there,
Tiberio is king.

38:49.293 --> 38:51.865
There are those who come here
and then break the law.

38:51.900 --> 38:53.735
Two gringos.

38:53.770 --> 38:56.265
They were robbing local farmers,
hiding up in the mountains.

38:56.300 --> 38:58.872
Tiberio and his men
hunted them down.

38:58.907 --> 39:01.369
I let them hang
for two weeks after that.

39:01.404 --> 39:03.272
The smell gets very bad.

39:03.307 --> 39:05.109
- Did you give them a trial?

39:06.750 --> 39:08.585
- It wasn't necessary.

39:16.122 --> 39:19.090
You should go over to the
hotel and get yourself a room.

39:21.765 --> 39:25.602
- Unfortunately, I am without
sufficient funds.

39:25.637 --> 39:27.032
- Yeah, I'll take care of that

39:27.067 --> 39:29.166
after I send a telegram
to your husband.

39:35.240 --> 39:37.273
See all this mess
you done caused?

39:37.308 --> 39:39.374
Runaway woman,

39:39.409 --> 39:42.784
bounty hunter,
price on your head...

39:44.348 --> 39:46.755
And believe me, for sure,
they'd rather see you dead.

39:46.790 --> 39:48.955
- Guess I was better off
in the army all those years

39:48.990 --> 39:50.627
taking nothing but shit.

39:50.662 --> 39:53.322
And knowing if I quit the army,

39:53.357 --> 39:56.567
I ain't got much chance
of doing nothing else.

39:56.602 --> 39:59.262
Except shining shoes
or serving food.

40:00.672 --> 40:02.199
Well no, sir.

40:03.433 --> 40:05.004
No thank you.

40:47.752 --> 40:49.213
Do you speak English?

40:49.248 --> 40:50.555
- I do, SeÃ±or.

40:50.590 --> 40:52.524
- Mrs. Kidd will need a room

40:52.559 --> 40:56.528
for a few days, maybe more.
I need a room as well.

40:57.993 --> 41:00.796
- Number four, at the top
of those stairs.

41:00.831 --> 41:02.325
- Thank you.

41:02.360 --> 41:05.229
- You have number two,
across the hallway.

41:05.264 --> 41:07.264
- Thanks.
- SeÃ±or.

41:11.941 --> 41:14.238
- I suppose I should say
thank you,

41:14.273 --> 41:16.746
but then I remember
who you're working for.

41:18.442 --> 41:20.244
It doesn't seem right,

41:20.279 --> 41:22.378
Elijah being treated
like a criminal,

41:22.413 --> 41:24.182
and I'm put up in a nice hotel.

41:25.625 --> 41:28.593
- Elijah left the army,
that makes him a deserter.

41:28.628 --> 41:32.223
You left your marriage.
No one goes to jail for that.

41:54.214 --> 41:56.445
- Ah, there he is.

41:56.480 --> 42:00.416
Joe Cribbens.
Professional card shark.

42:01.793 --> 42:03.628
See, I've been considering
our card game,

42:03.663 --> 42:05.190
and I believe you cheated me.

42:05.225 --> 42:07.962
- I don't need to cheat
to beat you, amigo.

42:07.997 --> 42:10.965
- Well, this time, I brought
my service revolver

42:11.000 --> 42:14.364
and I fully intend on dealing
with the situation.

42:14.399 --> 42:17.367
Now, I suggest you give me
back my money

42:17.402 --> 42:20.073
and throw in a few extra
shillings for good measure.

42:33.187 --> 42:37.453
- Goddamn Englishman
went and committed suicide.

42:57.508 --> 42:59.376
- Esperanza, you can come in.

43:01.182 --> 43:02.951
- I thought I picked...
Oh, I'm sorry.

43:02.986 --> 43:04.986
- No, come in.
- What I wanted to discuss--

43:05.021 --> 43:06.548
- I said come in.

43:11.698 --> 43:14.523
As you can see, I'm trying
to take a bath.

43:14.558 --> 43:16.701
My first real one in weeks.

43:19.805 --> 43:21.530
What's the matter?

43:21.565 --> 43:23.004
You suspect I'm a whore,

43:23.039 --> 43:24.874
I supposed I might
as well act like one.

43:27.307 --> 43:28.845
Are you getting nervous?

43:30.244 --> 43:32.849
Maybe, like most men,

43:32.884 --> 43:37.051
you're just scared to death of
really dealing with a woman.

43:37.086 --> 43:38.723
- Are you finished?

43:41.893 --> 43:44.190
I came to let you know
that tomorrow

43:44.225 --> 43:46.225
I'll start making arrangements

43:46.260 --> 43:48.326
to have you taken back
across the border.

43:50.396 --> 43:52.561
- My life is done there.

43:52.596 --> 43:55.135
I have to move on, not go back.

43:55.170 --> 43:57.500
I appreciate your concern,

43:57.535 --> 43:59.502
but I will be the one
to figure out my life.

44:01.011 --> 44:02.043
- Mm-hmm.

44:04.410 --> 44:06.718
You refuse to go?

44:06.753 --> 44:08.852
- I refuse to go.

44:09.613 --> 44:11.723
Even at gun point.

44:15.058 --> 44:18.290
If you'll excuse me.
- I'm sorry.

44:25.365 --> 44:26.595
As you have been told,

44:26.630 --> 44:28.498
I'm here representing
Tiberio Vargas.

44:28.533 --> 44:31.270
He has already heard about this
unfortunate incident.

44:31.305 --> 44:34.603
- Look, this man tried
to kill me, came here to do it.

44:34.638 --> 44:37.749
Most likely a real shit heel
in general.

44:37.784 --> 44:40.180
I figured I was doing
everybody a favor.

44:40.215 --> 44:43.755
- We need no favors,
but possibly you do.

44:43.790 --> 44:46.417
This man you killed
was doing serious business

44:46.452 --> 44:47.715
with Tiberio Vargas.

44:47.750 --> 44:50.256
- Tiberio Vargas,
I keep hearing the name.

44:50.291 --> 44:52.896
- Mmm, you do not want him
for an enemy.

45:02.974 --> 45:04.435
- Joe Cribbens.

45:06.472 --> 45:10.507
Name's not Joseph.
Just Joe will cover the deal.

45:11.180 --> 45:13.246
I was Texas, born and bred.

45:13.281 --> 45:15.743
Been knocking around
since I was 15.

45:15.778 --> 45:18.053
Worked Teamster, worked Trooper.

45:18.088 --> 45:19.791
Drifted some.

45:19.826 --> 45:21.859
I always liked playing cards.

45:23.258 --> 45:26.193
- Tell me why you shot
this Englishman.

45:27.966 --> 45:30.758
- I beat him at cards.
I beat him fair and square.

45:30.793 --> 45:32.595
He didn't take it too good.

45:32.630 --> 45:35.268
Guess I just turned out
to be the better man.

45:35.303 --> 45:38.436
- Luis agrees the Englishman
shot first.

45:38.471 --> 45:43.441
He's an honest man.
Tiberio will consider all this.

45:43.476 --> 45:45.311
You must wait here in Guadalupe

45:45.346 --> 45:47.643
while Tiberio makes
his decision.

45:48.514 --> 45:51.713
- Damn. My luck's run bad.

46:52.182 --> 46:55.546
- Mr. Borlund. We meet again.

46:55.581 --> 46:58.923
This time, I'm happy to say
I'm not sitting in a bathtub.

46:58.958 --> 47:00.749
