drink with me...

1:08:11.889 --> 1:08:13.460
I guess it's time...

1:08:14.529 --> 1:08:16.496
...to see how good
you really are.

1:08:16.531 --> 1:08:18.168
- Gonna have to take us both.

1:08:19.501 --> 1:08:21.666
- Your move, Joe.
- Gentlemen.

1:08:25.309 --> 1:08:28.475
My name is Rachel Kidd,
if it's of any interest.

1:08:28.510 --> 1:08:30.136
- Don't be getting in this,
ma'am.

1:08:30.171 --> 1:08:34.107
- He's right, Mrs. Kidd.
You best back away.

1:08:34.142 --> 1:08:36.285
- Mr. Borlund and I
have our differences.

1:08:36.320 --> 1:08:38.045
But he doesn't deserve
to be gunned down

1:08:38.080 --> 1:08:39.849
by a common criminal.

1:08:39.884 --> 1:08:42.456
- Oh, I'm not so common, ma'am.

1:08:42.491 --> 1:08:45.888
And even though you seem to
have a real unpleasant nature,

1:08:45.923 --> 1:08:48.858
I'd still hate to put
the finish on a woman.

1:08:49.498 --> 1:08:52.532
It ain't my style.

1:08:52.567 --> 1:08:55.095
- At this distance,
I don't think I'm going to miss.

1:08:56.197 --> 1:08:58.802
Now, listen to me
very carefully.

1:08:58.837 --> 1:09:00.870
I will not lose my nerve.

1:09:00.905 --> 1:09:02.707
I will pull the trigger.

1:09:02.742 --> 1:09:04.544
I promise.

1:09:13.390 --> 1:09:15.324
- You proud?

1:09:15.359 --> 1:09:18.921
Hiding behind a backup gun
and a woman.

1:09:19.726 --> 1:09:21.154
- Tell you what, Joe.

1:09:21.189 --> 1:09:23.563
I think I'd ride on out
before she gets nervous

1:09:23.598 --> 1:09:25.961
and accidentally
pulls the trigger.

1:09:27.602 --> 1:09:29.063
- Okay, amigo.

1:09:32.541 --> 1:09:35.036
I guess this hand goes to you.

1:09:35.071 --> 1:09:38.611
But... this ain't over yet.

1:09:52.594 --> 1:09:55.430
- Told you. Ain't got
nothing to worry about.

1:09:56.928 --> 1:09:59.269
- Once again, Mr. Poe,
very good.

1:10:00.338 --> 1:10:02.767
- Once good, I aim to please.

1:10:13.780 --> 1:10:17.419
- Guess it was a good thing
you gave me back my gun.

1:10:17.454 --> 1:10:20.114
- Joe was right.
This isn't over.

1:10:20.149 --> 1:10:24.393
But I appreciate what you did,
even though it was very foolish.

1:10:24.428 --> 1:10:27.660
- You probably saved my life
back in the cabin.

1:10:27.695 --> 1:10:29.464
I owed you.

1:10:29.499 --> 1:10:31.026
I try to pay my debts.

1:10:32.337 --> 1:10:34.832
I don't really drink,
but I think I need this.

1:10:45.647 --> 1:10:48.813
- Come to check
on the deserter man.

1:10:48.848 --> 1:10:51.618
- How long you figure
before Rachel's husband arrives?

1:10:52.489 --> 1:10:54.148
- About another day or two.

1:10:56.284 --> 1:10:58.218
- He better be bringing
his money.

1:11:48.578 --> 1:11:50.072
- Driver!

1:11:50.107 --> 1:11:51.414
Why in the hell
are we stopping?

1:11:51.449 --> 1:11:53.174
It's the middle of nowhere.

1:11:54.551 --> 1:11:56.177
- Hello, ladies.

1:11:56.212 --> 1:11:58.014
Martin Kidd, right?

1:11:59.050 --> 1:12:01.017
You step on out
and come with me.

1:12:01.052 --> 1:12:02.722
<i>Por favor.</i>

1:12:02.757 --> 1:12:05.461
Mr. Tiberio Vargas would like
to have a talk with you.

1:12:24.581 --> 1:12:29.045
I... speak English
a little bit.

1:12:29.883 --> 1:12:31.784
But only when I want to.

1:13:21.297 --> 1:13:22.362
<i>- Vamos.</i>

1:13:26.467 --> 1:13:29.402
- Mr. Kidd.
- Mr. Borlund!

1:13:29.437 --> 1:13:32.306
You're my welcoming party.
It's good to see you.

1:13:32.341 --> 1:13:33.945
How's my wife?

1:13:33.980 --> 1:13:36.409
- She's in the hotel
down the road.

1:13:36.444 --> 1:13:39.852
- Oh, that's where she is,
but how is she?

1:13:39.887 --> 1:13:43.526
- The past few weeks have been
very difficult for her.

1:13:44.562 --> 1:13:45.858
- And Elijah Jones?

1:13:45.893 --> 1:13:48.289
- He's in a jail cell
around the corner.

1:13:48.324 --> 1:13:52.029
- Good. I'll go visit Rachel
in due course,

1:13:52.064 --> 1:13:55.197
I'm in no hurry to deal
with her salacious conduct.

1:13:56.497 --> 1:13:59.366
Have you met this
Tiberio Vargas?

1:13:59.401 --> 1:14:02.204
- Only once.
- He's quite a fellow.

1:14:03.504 --> 1:14:06.648
Well, I owe you a debt
of gratitude

1:14:06.683 --> 1:14:08.551
for rounding up
these two runaways.

1:14:08.586 --> 1:14:10.014
- You owe me money.

1:14:10.049 --> 1:14:12.489
- Oh, I do. And you'll be paid.

1:14:13.316 --> 1:14:14.524
Paid in full.

1:14:58.933 --> 1:15:01.263
- If I may join you,
I wish to discuss with you

1:15:01.298 --> 1:15:03.540
the situation we find
ourselves in.

1:15:04.136 --> 1:15:05.674
- Then...

1:15:05.709 --> 1:15:08.534
I guess we oughta
discuss Tiberio,

1:15:08.569 --> 1:15:10.712
since nobody around here
can take a piss

1:15:10.747 --> 1:15:12.373
without him saying so.

1:15:12.408 --> 1:15:14.683
- Tiberio is of course
disappointed.

1:15:14.718 --> 1:15:16.949
He feels your tactics
were too bold.

1:15:16.984 --> 1:15:19.380
You were foolish and arrogant.

1:15:20.757 --> 1:15:23.087
I am here to tell you that

1:15:23.122 --> 1:15:26.156
Tiberio has no further need
of your services.

1:15:28.798 --> 1:15:30.490
You are dismissed.

1:15:31.966 --> 1:15:33.636
You're free to go.

1:16:29.056 --> 1:16:32.519
- One thing about you and
your kind, Mr. Cockroach,

1:16:32.554 --> 1:16:34.488
can't get rid of you, can we?

1:16:36.030 --> 1:16:38.833
Yes, sir, you sons of bitches

1:16:38.868 --> 1:16:42.166
must be first cousin
with Mr. Boll Weevil.

1:16:43.235 --> 1:16:45.466
And that means nothing much
good to be said.

1:16:46.304 --> 1:16:48.238
Just a goddamn nuisance.

1:17:12.330 --> 1:17:13.527
- Mr. Borlund.

1:17:14.068 --> 1:17:16.596
- Have you seen
your husband yet?

1:17:18.270 --> 1:17:22.008
I think he made some kind
of a deal with Tiberio Vargas,

1:17:22.043 --> 1:17:23.537
probably about you.

1:17:23.572 --> 1:17:25.880
I just wanted to make sure
you're alright.

1:17:28.577 --> 1:17:31.248
- I saw his arrival on
the overland from the parlor.

1:17:32.515 --> 1:17:35.384
It cost me a difficult moment.

1:17:35.419 --> 1:17:38.090
But I'm fine, Mr. Borlund.
Thank you for your concern.

1:17:41.293 --> 1:17:42.699
Just a moment.

1:17:52.040 --> 1:17:54.403
My last will and testament.

1:17:54.438 --> 1:17:57.043
My lawyer's name is on
the front of the envelope.

1:17:57.078 --> 1:17:59.749
To be delivered
in the event of my death.

1:18:17.725 --> 1:18:19.230
Yeah.

1:18:19.265 --> 1:18:20.770
Must be getting me
out of here.

1:18:20.805 --> 1:18:22.772
You know, I figured Tiberio

1:18:22.807 --> 1:18:26.776
would see the light.
Me and him, we got business.

1:18:32.850 --> 1:18:34.751
- Hello, Elijah.

1:18:36.150 --> 1:18:37.644
- Mr. Kidd.

1:18:39.956 --> 1:18:41.615
Now, uh...

1:18:44.587 --> 1:18:47.060
I can't say I expected you
to come down here.

1:18:47.095 --> 1:18:49.590
- No small talk, Elijah.

1:18:49.625 --> 1:18:51.262
It's time to pay you off.

1:18:54.135 --> 1:18:55.904
You gonna shoot
an unarmed man?

1:18:55.939 --> 1:18:57.807
- Yeah.

1:19:04.882 --> 1:19:06.849
Put a gun
in his hand.

1:19:06.884 --> 1:19:08.950
You open that cell door.

1:19:09.810 --> 1:19:11.447
He was trying to escape.

1:19:36.210 --> 1:19:37.308
He was dead

1:19:37.343 --> 1:19:39.079
when he fell to the floor
of his cell.

1:19:41.545 --> 1:19:42.984
- Poor Elijah.

1:19:57.528 --> 1:20:00.067
- Ah, Mr. Borlund. I expect
you've heard the news.

1:20:00.102 --> 1:20:03.939
US Army Private Elijah Jones
is no longer a problem.

1:20:04.436 --> 1:20:07.338
- How much did it cost
Mr. Kidd to commit this murder?

1:20:07.373 --> 1:20:09.472
- I'm investigating
these circumstances.

1:20:09.507 --> 1:20:11.705
- I am confused, Mr. Borlund.

1:20:11.740 --> 1:20:13.476
Who do you think
you're working for?

1:20:13.511 --> 1:20:16.215
- I work for myself.
Always have.

1:20:16.921 --> 1:20:18.580
- I was dishonored.

1:20:18.615 --> 1:20:20.890
A wife is not supposed
to run away from her husband

1:20:20.925 --> 1:20:22.518
with a common soldier.

1:20:22.553 --> 1:20:24.586
- You mean common
Black soldiers?

1:20:25.688 --> 1:20:27.754
- Yeah, that's exactly
what I mean.

1:20:27.789 --> 1:20:31.296
Common... Black... soldiers.

1:20:32.299 --> 1:20:34.068
- I tell you again,
I'm investigating--

1:21:33.195 --> 1:21:35.624
I'd like to see
my wife, Mrs. Rachel Kidd.

1:21:35.659 --> 1:21:37.934
Can you tell me her room number?

1:21:39.135 --> 1:21:40.970
- She's in number 4.

1:21:41.005 --> 1:21:42.697
Up the stairs.

1:22:06.459 --> 1:22:07.964
- Martin.

1:22:10.727 --> 1:22:15.334
- I am, uh... a bit slow
on coming to see you.

1:22:15.369 --> 1:22:17.336
Of course, there's no point
in pretending

1:22:17.371 --> 1:22:20.669
that there's any affection
between us, is there?

1:22:20.704 --> 1:22:23.177
- No. None at all.

1:22:25.313 --> 1:22:26.807
I take it you owe Mr. Borlund

1:22:26.842 --> 1:22:29.051
a great deal of money
for finding me.

1:22:29.086 --> 1:22:31.317
- Mr. Borlund will receive
what he's earned.

1:22:31.352 --> 1:22:34.617
- Just like Elijah?
Did he receive what he earned?

1:22:34.652 --> 1:22:37.323
- Uh, no. I was too good to him.
He died a quick death.

1:22:37.358 --> 1:22:39.556
- You are despicable, Martin.

1:22:42.594 --> 1:22:44.033
- You're breaking marriage vows.

1:22:44.068 --> 1:22:46.233
You run away with
an army deserter

1:22:46.268 --> 1:22:49.731
who's also a criminal low-life
demanding ransom money

1:22:49.766 --> 1:22:51.568
for your services to him
as a whore.

1:22:51.603 --> 1:22:54.373
You come very close
to jeopardizing my future

1:22:54.408 --> 1:22:56.507
political career
with this lurid scandal,

1:22:56.542 --> 1:22:59.411
and then you tell me
that I'm despicable?

1:22:59.446 --> 1:23:00.610
- I was stupid.

1:23:01.514 --> 1:23:03.151
I made bad situations worse

1:23:03.186 --> 1:23:04.911
which caused terrible
things to happen.

1:23:04.946 --> 1:23:06.682
I have no excuse.

1:23:06.717 --> 1:23:08.090
You just wanted legitimacy

1:23:08.125 --> 1:23:09.982
and the security
of my future inheritance.

1:23:10.017 --> 1:23:11.225
We never loved each other.

1:23:11.260 --> 1:23:12.820
- Hmm.
- It was all just

1:23:12.855 --> 1:23:14.360
mutual convenience.

1:23:14.395 --> 1:23:16.824
- I intend to return to Santa Fe

1:23:16.859 --> 1:23:19.563
where the story'll be put out
in the newspapers

1:23:19.598 --> 1:23:22.236
how I killed my wife's abductor
in a heroic act,

1:23:22.271 --> 1:23:24.403
but that she was unfortunately
captured and killed

1:23:24.438 --> 1:23:26.603
by a gang of Mexican outlaws,

1:23:26.638 --> 1:23:29.375
killed after, you know,
being used by them

1:23:29.410 --> 1:23:31.740
in the lowest possible ways.

1:23:31.775 --> 1:23:32.741
- Good story.

1:23:32.776 --> 1:23:34.248
Sad thing is a lot of people

1:23:34.283 --> 1:23:35.513
will probably believe it.

1:23:35.548 --> 1:23:37.009
- It's gonna be quite close
to the truth.

1:23:37.044 --> 1:23:39.451
Given your appetite,
you might enjoy being fucked

1:23:39.486 --> 1:23:43.884
up, down and sideways by those
<i>vaqueros</i> before they kill you.

1:23:43.919 --> 1:23:45.424
They will of course kill you.

1:23:45.459 --> 1:23:49.824
No, it's part of my
understanding with SeÃ±or Vargas.

1:23:50.662 --> 1:23:53.432
- You think I'll go willingly?
- Oh no.

1:23:54.237 --> 1:23:57.865
But these men are quite
happy to use force.

1:23:57.900 --> 1:23:59.999
And you have nowhere to hide.

1:24:02.069 --> 1:24:06.313
I'll leave you now
to think about your future.

1:24:08.614 --> 1:24:11.186
- I don't think it's going
to work out the way you want.

1:24:13.982 --> 1:24:15.949
- You won't do it.

1:24:15.984 --> 1:24:18.556
You don't actually
have the nerve to kill a man.

1:24:18.591 --> 1:24:20.129
- I've changed.

1:24:20.164 --> 1:24:23.022
And you always underestimate me.

1:24:24.091 --> 1:24:26.729
- I repeat... You won't do--

1:24:50.788 --> 1:24:52.722
I heard a shot!
Are you...

1:24:55.397 --> 1:24:57.364
- I've killed my husband.

1:25:00.336 --> 1:25:02.699
- Well, you gave him
what he deserved.

1:25:02.734 --> 1:25:04.569
He killed Elijah.

1:25:06.133 --> 1:25:07.473
- Yes.

1:25:09.345 --> 1:25:11.070
I'm not sorry.

1:26:34.155 --> 1:26:35.990
Knock next time!

1:28:38.048 --> 1:28:39.245
I assume...

1:28:39.951 --> 1:28:42.182
...you intend to defend
Mrs. Kidd?

1:28:42.217 --> 1:28:44.217
- And I imagine you have
a nice safe spot

1:28:44.252 --> 1:28:45.757
picked out for yourself.

1:28:45.792 --> 1:28:47.759
- I will ignore your insult.

1:28:48.729 --> 1:28:50.762
And I promise you
I will do my duty today

1:28:50.797 --> 1:28:52.159
as an officer of the law.

1:28:52.194 --> 1:28:54.634
- Just like you did
with Elijah Jones?

1:28:55.395 --> 1:28:57.131
- That was my mistake.

1:28:57.771 --> 1:29:00.706
I should have realized Mr. Kidd
intended to kill Elijah.

1:29:01.808 --> 1:29:03.412
He bribed my deputy.

1:29:06.142 --> 1:29:07.449
I am ashamed.

1:33:01.608 --> 1:33:03.410
I'm taking you
out, mister.

1:33:03.445 --> 1:33:05.852
- Alright then,
go ahead and try.

1:34:32.435 --> 1:34:34.600
I thought
that you were smarter...

1:34:37.242 --> 1:34:39.539
...than getting
in the middle of this.

1:34:50.552 --> 1:34:53.157
Ride out of here
before I decide to shoot you.

1:34:53.797 --> 1:34:55.830
- I thank you for your
courtesy and kindness.

1:35:28.788 --> 1:35:30.425
- Tiberio Vargas!

1:35:52.350 --> 1:35:53.822
Yah!

1:36:14.174 --> 1:36:15.635
- Tiberio!

1:36:16.077 --> 1:36:17.604
Just want to tell you,

1:36:17.639 --> 1:36:19.672
since I'm not working
for you anymore,

1:36:19.707 --> 1:36:22.180
I think you're shit.

1:36:22.215 --> 1:36:23.709
Always did.

1:36:36.196 --> 1:36:37.558
Guess what?

1:36:37.593 --> 1:36:39.791
I did you a favor, bounty man.

1:36:39.826 --> 1:36:43.498
You're gonna thank me
for killing my old boss?

1:36:45.370 --> 1:36:47.942
He was gonna spoil
my fun with you.

1:36:50.573 --> 1:36:52.914
- About time you did
something good.

1:37:01.881 --> 1:37:04.024
You know, you can
ride out of here, Joe.

1:37:06.094 --> 1:37:08.358
- I took his money.

1:37:08.393 --> 1:37:10.063
Maybe ought to earn it.

1:37:11.297 --> 1:37:14.364
Besides, there's no avoiding it.

1:37:15.301 --> 1:37:17.499
You and me got a reckoning.

1:37:17.534 --> 1:37:21.338
- I'm giving you a clean start.
Don't be a damn fool!

1:37:21.373 --> 1:37:23.406
- Amigo...

1:37:23.441 --> 1:37:25.375
I was born a fool.

1:37:33.451 --> 1:37:35.385
I'll be a son of a bitch.

1:37:36.993 --> 1:37:38.586
You killed me.

1:37:43.791 --> 1:37:45.395
Luck ran out.

1:37:47.300 --> 1:37:49.234
I'm just dying.

1:37:52.140 --> 1:37:54.206
Happens to us all.

1:37:54.241 --> 1:37:55.438
Don't it?

1:38:21.004 --> 1:38:22.399
- Mr. Poe.

1:38:24.370 --> 1:38:26.436
- Mr. Borlund.

1:38:33.346 --> 1:38:35.610
- I'm gonna make sure
that your body gets sent

1:38:35.645 --> 1:38:38.316
back to the army. They'll give
you a proper finish,

1:38:38.351 --> 1:38:40.318
bugle, flags...

1:38:40.353 --> 1:38:41.814
A man can do worse.

1:38:41.849 --> 1:38:43.783
- Goddamit. I...

1:38:43.818 --> 1:38:45.719
I've been shot,
but I ain't dying.

1:38:46.887 --> 1:38:49.789
Just make sure the damn doctor
don't cut my arm off.

1:38:50.561 --> 1:38:52.462
- Yeah, you have my word.

1:39:05.246 --> 1:39:07.147
Your husband's dead.

1:39:09.580 --> 1:39:12.581
He was obviously shot
by Tiberio's men.

1:39:16.356 --> 1:39:19.060
- You really think
the truth won't come out?

1:39:20.360 --> 1:39:21.689
- Who's to ask?

1:39:22.659 --> 1:39:24.197
Well, who is to tell?

1:39:28.434 --> 1:39:31.237
Oh, you need that looked after.

1:39:31.272 --> 1:39:33.206
It's gonna take a few stitches.

1:39:34.737 --> 1:39:37.441
- I'll wear my scar
as a badge of honor.

1:39:38.543 --> 1:39:40.444
- Mm-hmm.

1:39:43.185 --> 1:39:44.877
I need a drink.
